      <div class="subfield"><strong>$2 - Source</strong> <div class="description">MARC code that identifies the source list for the abbreviated title, if the source
                              is known. Used primarily when the second indicator position contains value 0. It
                              may also be added when the second indicator contains value blank and another
                              abbreviated title list uses the same abbreviation as the abbreviated key
                           title.
         </div>
         <div class="description2">
            <div class="description">Code from: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/standards/sourcelist/abbreviated-title.html">Abbreviated Title Source Codes </a></em>.
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="example">
