      <div class="subfield"><strong>$6 - Linkage</strong> <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                                       Subfields</a></em>.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$8 - Field link and sequence number</strong> 
        <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                                       Subfields</a></em>.
        </div>
   </div>
      <hr>
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Punctuation</strong> - Field 210 does not end with a mark of punctuation unless the last word in the field is
                     an abbreviation, initial/letter, or data that ends with a mark of punctuation. See also
                     subfield descriptions for punctuation information.
      </div>
      <hr>
      <h3>CONTENT DESIGNATOR HISTORY</h3>
      <div class="font_small"><em>Indicator 1 - Title added entry [NEW, 1977]</em><br>Records created prior to the definition of the first indicator in 1977 may contain #
                        meaning <em>undefined</em> in this position.<br>
                        <em>Indicator 2 - Type [NEW, 1998]</em><br>
                        When the field was redefined to include non-key title abbreviations in 1998, value
                        blank was redefined to identify key titles. Value blank in pre 1998 records also
                        identifies key titles since only key title abbreviations allowed in the field before
                        that date.
      </div>
